				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">On the 5th write the shift register shifts, but the 8/A/C/E data register is updated more or less at the same moment so the final shift won't corrupt the register. Using flip flops with enable instead of clock gating with a decoder will ensure that the data register is updated safely, but the timing isn't that critical and I really doubt a chip designer back then would use so many gates.</div>

